        <p><b>Item #:</b> SCP-6298 </p>

        <p><b>Object Class:</b> Keter </p>

        <p><b>Special Containment Procedures:</b> SCP-6298-1 instances are to be quarantined at location of discovery. Where local quarantine is rendered logistically impractical or locationally unfeasible, instances are to be relocated to Site-14 within hermetically sealed Impromptu Isolation Chambers. Task force members interacting with SCP-6298-1 instances for this purpose are to be equipped with Mk.2 Foundation PPPS (positive pressure personnel suits) at all times.</p>

        <p> SCP-6298-α is to remain within Sterile Cleanroom Partition Zeta at Site-14 for observation and testing. Under no circumstances are any attending personnel to interact directly with SCP-6298-α, or any item SCP-6298-α has come in contact with. </p>

        <p>SCP-6298 containment efforts are to focus on isolating the pathogen responsible for the communication of the SCP-6298 phenomenon.</p>

        <p><b>Description:</b> SCP-6298 is a transmissible phenomenon of interpersonal abstraction caused by noöspheric entanglement and semantic covalence. Individuals infected with SCP-6298 (hereafter referred to as SCP-6298-1 instances) experience a progressive and rapid dissolution of personal identity, both semantically and conceptually. Simultaneously, the romantic partner of the SCP-6298-1 instance will experience the same dissolution, until they are noöspherically indistinguishable. </p>

        <p>SCP-6298-1 instances under observation have noted no sense of self-alienation or emotional distress associated with 
        <a href="https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-7783" target="_blank">other anomalies resulting in a loss of individualised conceptual coherency</a>. Counterintuitively, the majority of observed instances report a general feeling of fulfillment and a contented haziness. The reasons for this discrepancy are poorly understood at this time.</p>

        <p>SCP-6298-α is the collective designation for the two discrete entities under the collective identity Dr. Jacques Vincent Gardener. SCP-6298-α is an adult man of Hispanic American heritage, formerly employed by the Site-14 Administration and Oversight department. Identically, SCP-6298-α is an adult man of Germanic European descent, who was formerly employed by the Site-14 Janitorial department. As all currently observed infections have been contact traced to SCP-6298-α, transmission of the SCP-6298 phenomenon is believed to be pathogenic in nature. SCP-6298-α is currently held in a secure clean room at Site-14, where experimentation is underway to isolate and identify the SCP-6298 pathogen.</p>

