        <p>SCP-6298-1 instances under observation have noted no sense of self-alienation or emotional distress associated with 
        <a href="https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-7783" target="_blank">other anomalies resulting in a loss of individualised conceptual coherency</a>. Counterintuitively, the majority of observed instances report a general feeling of fulfillment and a contented haziness. The reasons for this discrepancy <s>are poorly understood at this time</s> <span style="color:red;"> are suspected to result from a secondary memetic component of SCP-6298 infection </p>

        <p>SCP-6298-α is the collective designation for the two discrete entities under the collective identity Dr. Jacques Vincent Gardener. SCP-6298-α is an adult man of Hispanic American heritage, formerly employed by the Site-14 Administration and Oversight department. Identically, SCP-6298-α is an adult man of Germanic European descent, who was formerly employed by the Site-14 Janitorial department. <s> As all currently observed infections have been contact traced to SCP-6298-α, transmission of the SCP-6298 phenomenon is believed to be pathogenic in nature. SCP-6298-α is currently held in a secure clean room at Site-14, where experimentation is underway to isolate and identify the SCP-6298 pathogen.</s></p>

        <p><span style="color:red;">Following confirmed transmission from SCP-6298-α to his remote attending physician, Dr. Joanna Hernandez, who had never interacted physically with SCP-6298-α, the dedicated research staff have reassessed the possible infection vectors. The most likely source of transmission is an unidentified memetic or infohazardous component to the SCP-6298 phenomenon, as the only evident connection between Hernandez and SCP-6298-α is mono-directional observation of the initially infected instance. Primary research efforts into the anomaly have been transferred to Site-82, and the containment procedures updated.</span></p>


        <p><span style="color:red;">In addition to contradicting prior assumptions about SCP-6298's transmission vectors, the infection of Dr. Hernandez overturned previously established understanding of the infection. Internal Foundation records indicate Dr. Hernandez is both asexual and aromantic. As a result, it was believed that, even should the dissolutive effects of SCP-6298 take place, the subsequent interpersonal abstraction would have no secondary instance to act upon. Contrary to expectations, upon contraction of SCP-6298, the abstractive symptoms of the phenomenon were noted to impact her close confidant and childhood friend, Dr. Joanna Hernandez. The two have subsequently been relocated to Site-82 for further study.</p>

