        <p><s>Current containment procedures have failed to contain the proliferation of SCP-6298-1 instances. Research efforts have been diffused to all researchers specialising in noöspheric, semantospheric, and conceptual spaces. The SCP-6298 research project has been elevated to Alpha Priority. All available resources have been committed to the completion of the Conceptual Luxation and Organo-Semiotic Egress FilTer.When completed, the device will enable perfect semiotic isolation of all remaining individualised identities, and prevent all forms of interpersonal semantic dissolution.</s></p>

        <p><span style="color:red;">Transmission of the SCP-6298 phenomenon is inevitable.</p>


        <p><b>Event-6298-IK:</b></p>

        <p><span style="color:red;">On 19/12/24, an SCP-6298 mass transmission event occured in the Seattle Metropolitan Area, centered around an individual designated SCP-6298-β, the brother of Senior Researcher David Chen-- head of the Site-27 Conceptual Luxation and Organo-Semiotic Egress FilTer development sub-team. Due to SCP-6298-β's membership of a network of interconnected polyamorous relationships in the Seattle area, roughly 18,000 discrete instances of SCP-6298-β now inhabit the city and surrounding regions. Attempts at Black Swan Scenario modelling had proceeded on the prior observation of bilateral secondary infection. As a result, no contingency planning had accounted for the prospect of multilateral infection, let alone on the scale of Event-6298-IK.</p>

        <p><span style="color:red;">MTF units were deployed as soon as the Foundation were made aware of the outbreak and attempts to contain SCP-6298-β instances were underway within 24 hours. However, the scale and diffusion of the epidemic hampered containment efforts. A mass scale information control campaign in conjunction with local news networks and government proved ineffective at limiting the spread of SCP-6298 awareness. Mass termination of newly-infected SCP-6298-1 instances within the Greater Seattle Area proved infeasible, as the scale of operations would invariably constitute a full collapse of the Veil as it currently exists.</p>

        <p><span style="color:red;">As a result of Foundation inability to prevent or limit SCP-6298 transmission, current R0 observations indicate 19 days until all extant humans represent SCP-6298-1 instances. Following the submission of these findings, the containment class has been upgraded to Apollyon. Faced with the choice between a BK-Class "Broken Veil" Scenario, and an IK-Class "End of Individuality" Scenario, a full quorum of the O5 Council has voted to abandon SCP-6298 containment measures.</p>
